Defendant Jaquayle M Newton in court.  Attorney Corey R. Flynn in court for Jaquayle M Newton.  Prosecuting attorney Navjot Singh Hira in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a final pretrial. State has filed an amended criminal complaint. Defense move to dismiss counts 3 and 4. Arguments heard. Court grants defense's motion. Counts 3 and 4 are dismissed due to lack of probable cause. Court reviewed the Amended complaint and found probable cause as to counts 1, 2 and 5. Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to Defendant's attorney. Defendant plead not guilty.  Case remains in trial posture, Court advises the parties that the jury trial will have to be rescheduled, Court vacates the scheduled jury trial. Parties are advised that effective 10/31/2022, pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-17, this case will be reassigned to Branch 37, Judge Dee in Room 515 of the Courthouse.
